# Human Detection & Auto Firing System — Advanced Level Completion

## Background

The current project has a basic Jupyter notebook (`MAIN.IPYNB`) with:
- YOLOv8 pose model (`yolov8n-pose.pt`) for shoulder keypoint detection
- YOLOv8 face model (`yolov8n-face.pt`) for face detection
- Basic heart location estimation (midpoint of shoulders + offset)
- Simple webcam loop with OpenCV display

**Problems with current code:**
- Runs only in Jupyter notebook (not production-ready)
- No error handling for missing keypoints / low-confidence detections
- Heart estimation uses hardcoded pixel offsets (fails at different distances/scales)
- No tracking, no target locking, no firing simulation
- No HUD / military-style overlay
- No logging or recording capabilities

---

## Proposed Changes

### Architecture: Modular Python Application

Convert from a single notebook cell to a professional, modular Python project:

```
DRDO PROJECT - Copy/
├── main.py                    # Entry point
├── config.py                  # All configurable parameters
├── core/
│   ├── __init__.py
│   ├── detector.py            # Human/Face/Pose detection engine
│   ├── heart_estimator.py     # Anatomical heart position calculator
│   ├── tracker.py             # Multi-target tracking with IDs
│   └── firing_system.py       # Simulated firing & engagement logic
├── ui/
│   ├── __init__.py
